The 2018 MyBroadband Conference and Expo will take place at the Gallagher Convention Centre on 18 October, and it is a must-attend event for IT executives and managers. It is the premier IT and telecoms event in South Africa, with speakers and exhibitors from South Africa’s top ICT companies. Delegates will gain insight about the local ICT market from top speakers, including Vodacom CEO Shameel Joosub, Liquid Telecom CEO Reshaad Sha, and MTN SA CEO Godfrey Motsa. Other speakers include Telkom’s Serame Taukobong, Nokia Software’s Raghav Sahgal, Vodacom innovation head Jannie van Zyl, and SqwidNet CEO Phathizwe Malinga. South Africa’s top telecommunications and IT companies have partnered with MyBroadband as exhibitors for the event. All conference delegates will receive a voucher booklet with special deals on telecommunications and IT products in the business market from these exhibitors. Delegates can also interact with these companies to find out what the best IT or telecoms solution is for their business. The conference costs R1,995 to attend, but MyBroadband readers can receive a big discount on the normal rate using the special voucher code below. The tickets cover all aspects of the event, including access to the expo and conference, lunch, and refreshments.